
Overview of noun correction

The noun correction has 7 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (2) correction, rectification -- (the act of offering an improvement to replace a mistake; setting right)
2. (1) correction, fudge factor -- (a quantity that is added or subtracted in order to increase the accuracy of a scientific measure)
3. (1) correction -- (something substituted for an error)
4. correction, chastening, chastisement -- (a rebuke for making a mistake)
5. correction -- (a drop in stock market activity or stock prices following a period of increases; "market runups are invariably followed by a correction")
6. discipline, correction -- (the act of punishing; "the offenders deserved the harsh discipline they received")
7. correction -- (treatment of a specific defect; "the correction of his vision with eye glasses")
